<br>
I'm about to max out of bg3 and I'm going to have 10 rsps to play around with.  When I'm level 50, the first 2 abilities I want to get are Purge and FA2/IP.  So I was wondering, what do you guys suggest I buy with my points now.  The way I see it I have 3 options:<br>
<br>
1) Get Purge now<br>
2) Get FA2 now in preparation for IP<br>
3) Get passives now and respec when I hit 50.<br>
<br>
I figure passives would probably be the best way to go in terms of helping me level... but of course I'd then have to use a respec.  Also, if passives are the way to go which should I get?  MoPain?  Any help here would be appreciated as I am still a Skald (and for that matter Midgard) noob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=courtjester@teamskald>CourtJester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/25/03 3:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=777.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Purge.</span><hr size=1> IMHO, Purge is, for a Skald, the most important RA, even more than IP. With the lack of determination, and the tendency of fights to last no more than 1 minute, a mezz can render you totally useless.<br>
<br>
Purge, even in BG3, and despite of it's timer, will benefit you more than any passive. When I go group 8v8 RvR, I run straight for the bard/minstrel, usually not giving them a chance to mezz my whole group. I usually get stunned/mezzed before or after hitting them, but I purge immediately and snare my target, while the rest of my group are busy with /assist hitting the healers/casters.<br>
<br>
I spent my realm points on passives when I was lower level, and when I needed the RA respec at RR4 I didn't have it. That mistake cost me a handful of plats, and it's a pain, believe me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naeil>Naeil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/2/04 12:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=777.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Purge.</span><hr size=1> My first RA where FA and MCL. I found them to help out a ton when I was lvling up. My theory is &quot;Get what you can afford to help you lvl and respec later&quot; You do recieve 2 free RA respecs I believe.<br>
<br>
To go purge right away won't help you much lvling. You need FA anyways to get IP so you might as well go with that first. <br>
<br>
As for MCL its really not needed but I do like to have it. was nice to be able to gain mana back after I was rezed or if there was a long fight.<br>
<br>
Just my Oppinion, Hope it helps a bit! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singdemsong>Singdemsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://camelot.dragonzones.com/sig/ns.jpg " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/2/04 12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=777.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://camelot.dragonzones.com/sig/ns.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Purge.</span><hr size=1> Purge, while valuable in rvr, is not going to do much for you while you level up from 35 to 50.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.dravness.com/x.daoc/sig-sing.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/2/04 1:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=777.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Purge.</span><hr size=1> Purge for RvR.<br>
<br>
But if you have an RA respec available and want to help yourself get levelled faster, I'd suggest MCL and Aug Dex/MoPain.<br>
<br>
If you plan on running any RvR before you hit 50, make sure to get Longwind 1.  You'll be a hinderance to any group without it.<br>
<br>
